Real Madrid have confirmed captain Sergio Ramos is leaving the club. The Spanish giants also announced a press conference will be held on Thursday, to bid farewell to the defender. Ramos’ contract expires at the end of June and there have been reports Real were willing to give him an extension if he accepted a pay cut. Sergio Ramos to leave Real Madrid
But the 35-year-old has decided to leave the Santiago Bernabeu after 16 years. “Real Madrid CF announces that tomorrow, Thursday, June 17, at 12:30 pm, there will be an institutional act of tribute and farewell to our captain Sergio Ramos, with the presence of our president Florentino Perez,” an official statement read. Ramos has been linked with Manchester City and Paris Saint-Germain.